    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Oil Pan and Oil Suction Tube -
        Installation - Installing the Oil Pan
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="4">
        <title>Installing the Oil Pan</title>
        <figure id="f26507install06" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
            <caption>RTV sealant locations, see inset (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front cover (front half)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front cover (rear half)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Sealant, Wacker T-442, (6 locations)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel housing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a circular dab of T-442 Wacker RTV sealant approximately 19 mm (0.75 in) in diameter
                to the six locations on the crankcase mounting surface. These locations coincide with gasketed joints
                between the front cover halves, crankcase and flywheel housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26507install03" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the oil pan gasket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before the RTV sealant dries (tack free), install a new oil pan gasket on the crankcase
                mounting surface. Make sure that the dowel on the gasket is aligned with the hole on the crankcase
                mounting surface.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26507install05" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the oil pan</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil pan onto the crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26507install08" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing oil pan mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 18 oil pan mounting bolts (M8 x 24). Tighten all bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_152.xml" xrefid="t07002" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
